race.comment: Time for the Guineas now where the exciting KING OF LIGHT (1) aims to remain unbeaten. Getting out to the mile now is a big tick and he maps to get a perfect run in transit. He'll need to raise the bar again, but his sectionals say that he can and he's clearly the one to beat. ROCK FEST (4) wound up nicely late in the Fairetha and should be much-improved here second-up and out to the mile. Suspect they'll try and sit closer to KING OF LIGHT this time around and with improvement on the cards, he looks the main danger. HEEZA PHOENIX (3) looked the winner in the Fairetha but was gunned down late by KING OF LIGHT. He'll be better for that effort and his front-running style can see him dictate out to the mile now. Rise in trip looks no issue and he'll take catching. BUTHELEZI (10) looks a nice horse on the rise. Will need to improve no but can be thereabouts. MARDUSA (2) comes through the Fairetha where he wasn't far off and is worth including.
